         <abstract>
            <p>A short Gǝʿǝz theological treatise - a translation from Arabic. In the early Church this kind of text was recited for the baptized faithful after the catechumens had been dismissed. 
               Whilst <persName ref="PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName>, as the central celebrated ﬁgure, 
               was described and praised without his name being mentioned directly, the initiated in the mysteries of the Christian faith knew who was intended.</p>
         </abstract>
